olive oil
1 carrot
1 bag broccoli florets
1 packet basmati rice
1 packet beef mince
1 egg
1 sachet curry powder
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 sachet chermoula spice blend
1 packet coconut milk
1 bag mint

• Boil the kettle. Thinly slice carrot into sticks. Cut any larger broccoli florets in half.
• Half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water. Add basmati rice and a pinch of salt and cook, uncovered, over high heat until tender, 12 minutes.
• Place a colander or steamer basket on top of saucepan, then add broccoli and carrot.
• Cover with a lid and steam until tender, 6-7 minutes.
• Drain rice and set aside. Transfer veggies to a medium bowl and season to taste. Cover to keep warm.

• In a second medium bowl, combine beef mince, the egg, curry powder, fine breadcrumbs and a pinch of salt. Using damp hands, shape beef mixture into koftas (3-4 per person).
• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook koftas, turning, until browned and cooked through, 8-10 minutes (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded). Transfer to a plate.

• Wipe out the frying pan, then return to medium heat.
• Add chermoula spice blend and coconut milk and cook, stirring, until thickened, 1-2 minutes. Remove from heat.

• Divide rapid rice, steamed veggies and beef koftas between plates.
• Spoon Moroccan coconut sauce over koftas. Tear over mint to serve. Enjoy!